review_blob: This is awful, omg what did they do to the beer?  My flatmate got given heaps for free and had so much trouble trying to get through it all.
A lovely larger, enjoyed on various pub crawls.  Great when one cant stand drinking beers like Guiness.  Goes down easily.

When in Hamilton... 
A festive beer especially when drunk in large quantities, always leads to a good night but not necessarily rememberable.

A legendary drink but unfortunately not to my liking.  I love the look of it but just find it really difficult to drink.  Have never made it to the bottom of the glass.  Perhaps more practice is needed.
A bitter beer, lovingly enjoyed by Engineering students.  However a bit to harsh for my palate.  I only drink it when its subsidised or free.
Interesting flavour, not sure if its quite my style.  The boys like it for a change from their usual.

Better alternative to Export Gold, smells and tates so much nicer.
Easy to drink and everyones happy.

Refreshing cider, easy to drink.
Great to have at a Keg party, gets a bit messy though.
A unique beer, I drink it on special occasions (or whenever Im at a Belgin Beer cafe) love the taste, easy to drink.
The best thing about this beer is the price.  A beer favoured by students on a tight budget.

A great beer for drinking in mass quantities.  Regurgitates easily allowing more quantity to be drunk.  In a land where who drinks most is best this is an essential part of ones drinking experience.  This beer is most comminly seen at University parties.
